    {
      "id": "7a548aaa85d248045b8c1f485b562f8a1f3a3948",
      "author": {
        "_account_id": 11,
        "name": "Michael MacDonald",
        "email": "michael.macdonald@intel.com",
        "username": "mjmac",
        "inactive": true
      },
      "date": "2014-03-03 12:13:53.000000000",
      "message": "Patch Set 4:\n\nHmm. I see that. We could increase the timeout to 3x interval (15s). I am concerned about just continuing to increase the timeout, though. Seems like it is possibly covering up some other problem.\n\nAll that having been said, though, I see now that I have two inconsistent checks of the elapsed time. When I rewrote the test, I probably should have removed the second one. In this case, the first check is OK (update occurred before $progress_timeout), but the second check failed $elapsed > $progress_timeout. We don't have the xtrace output to be sure, but I assume that the check just barely failed.",
      "accounts_in_message": [],
      "_revision_number": 4
    },
